(
<figureCitation box="[160,229,1335,1361]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
