<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="262" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1406,2045]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1406,1433]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This new species is only known from the female; the mandible is five-toothed, the second recurrent vein ends distal to second submarginal crossvein, the subantennal suture is slightly outwardly arcuate, and the scutellum is broadly rounded but emarginate medially, the lateral margin of axilla convex, so it belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Trachusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Paraanthidium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Paraanthidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new species is very similar to 
<emphasis box="[658,674,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">T</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[686,863,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Trachusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis" subGenus="Paraanthidium">
(
<emphasis box="[696,713,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[735,863,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[1231,1247,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">T</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[1260,1437,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Trachusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis" subGenus="Paraanthidium">
(
<emphasis box="[1269,1286,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1309,1437,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: Clypeus without a shining longitudinal slightly elevated middle line, with fine and dense punctures (
<figureCitation box="[345,433,1587,1613]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
); pronotal lobe small and without obvious sharp lamella directed upwards, distinct medial bump of similar height to carina (
<figureCitation box="[527,617,1623,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); apical half disc of T4 yellow, not black (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1174,1623,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1406,2045]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,153,540]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="262" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1658,1685]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Description:</emphasis>
Female, BL=9.0–10.0 mm (
<figureCitation box="[673,765,1659,1685]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
); head broader than long, HW: HL=79: 72 (
<figureCitation box="[1271,1360,1659,1685]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
); gena narrower than eye, GW: EW=12: 18; MtW: MsW=95: 83 (
<figureCitation box="[830,921,1695,1721]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[935,1023,1695,1721]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
); ocelloccipital distance longer than ocellocular distance, OCD: OOD=15: 9. Clypeus broader than long, concave with apical margin slightly emargin- ate in middle, without a shining longitudinal slightly elevated middle line starting from basal to middle of clypeus, punctures fine and dense (
<figureCitation box="[439,526,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
); subantennal suture slightly arcuate outwardly (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1151,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
); mandible dull, minutely roughened and bearing very short hairs, broadened apically, with five black teeth; vertex polished and shining, with sparse and rounded punctures (
<figureCitation box="[555,643,1875,1901]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
); omaulus distinctly angled but lacking carina, anterior surface weakly concave if at all; pronotal lobe lamellate, but relatively small, without obvious sharp lamella directed upwards (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); scutum polished and shining, with large and dense rounded punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1105,1947,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); scutellum broadly rounded, emarginate medially, overhanging metanotum, with dense and rounded punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1162,1983,2009]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); lateral margin of axilla convex, with punctures similar to those of scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[765,856,2019,2045]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); disc of T1–T3 with dense and rounded punctures (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
); vein cu-v of hind wing oblique, nearly half as long as second abscissa of M+Cu (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1235,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,177,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1438,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Trachusa (Paraanthidium) pingdaensis Niu, sp. nov., A–H, female. A: Body in lateral view; B: Head in frontal view; C: Supraclypeal area in frontal view, showing subantennal suture; D: Mesosoma in dorsal view; E: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T1–T3; F: Metasoma in dorsal view, showing T4–T6; G: Fore wing in frontal view, showing the position of the second recurrent vein; H: Hind wing in frontal view, showing vein cu–v and f M+Cu. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3349443/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Fig. 9H</figureCitation>
), second recurrent vein of fore wing ends distal to second submarginal crossvein (
